id: pm-p9a4
title: "Wave 0 graph baseline and waiver ledger: classify roots, active dependency isolates, legacy aliases, and body-to-edge drift"
description: Publish a reproducible all-status graph baseline and classify every currently suspicious sparse or semantically ambiguous case before changing relationships.
type: Task
status: open
priority: 1
tags[5]: baseline,graph,relationships,task,"wave:0"
created_at: "2026-07-13T21:59:48.347Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T21:59:48.347Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 300
acceptance_criteria: "Record snapshot identity, commands, schema and package versions, counts by status and type, parent-depth distribution, edge kinds, components, isolates, ordering depth, dangling endpoints, and history integrity; Classify all roots and active dependency isolates as intentional, governed sparse, incomplete, ambiguous, archived, or remediation debt with reason and reviewer state; Detect item bodies and comments that name explicit prerequisites or delivery links missing from dependency metadata and record source excerpts or event pointers without auto-mutating; Map related_to and other legacy aliases plus parent or child duplication into candidate canonical kinds while preserving uncertainty; Produce cursorable machine-readable findings and a compact summary whose limits, omissions, and snapshot are explicit; Run exact, fuzzy, and parent-scope duplicate scans plus validate, health, and history-drift checks; baseline creation makes no terminal-item mutations"
goal: project management = context management
objective: Turn audit counts into a deterministic evidence and waiver ledger that later waves can safely execute
value: Every proposed graph change starts from a reviewed finding rather than a density target or intuition
impact: "Prevents synthetic links and makes reconstruction resumable, measurable, and multi-agent safe"
outcome: "Versioned baseline metrics, exact item classifications, waiver reasons, body-to-edge findings, and proposed remediation records"
why_now: "The current baseline has 185 hierarchy roots overall, 100 active dependency isolates, alias drift, and documented prerequisites absent from metadata"
parent: pm-a8zm
risk: low
confidence: high
