comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T21:59:48.347Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: prior audits captured point-in-time state but no open execution task owns the typed graph baseline,isolate classification,waiver ledger,and body-to-edge drift required by pm-a8zm."
body: "## Current reproducible anchors\n\nAt audit time: 1,786 total items; 200 active; 1,601 parent edges; 1,137 dependency entries; 665 items with dependencies; 109 active dependency components; 100 active dependency isolates; longest active order-bearing path two edges; parent depth max four; no active normalized-title duplicate cluster; no active lifecycle cycle or dangling dependency endpoint.\n\nThese are baselines, not target quotas. The task must rerun and timestamp every measure when claimed.\n\n## Deliverables\n\nA counts-first report, machine-readable finding stream, waiver registry, explicit uncertainty queue, and exact proposed relationship operations for Wave 1."
